{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-05-01T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At the far edge of Ynys Llanddwyn, where the land quietly gives way to sea, Tŵr Mawr Lighthouse stands watch without making a fuss. It is not tall, not flashy, but it knows its purpose—and it keeps it bright.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_EN-CA5457397043_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_EN-CA5457397043_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Light at the end of the isle","Title":"Tŵr Mawr Lighthouse, Ynys Llanddwyn, Anglesey, Wales","Copyright":"© Lukas Bischoff/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/53.13707,-4.412761/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=53.13707,-4.412761;S9;Ynys Llanddwyn, Isle of Anglesey, Wales&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260501_TwrMawrLighthouse2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Twr+Mawr+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260501_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260501_TwrMawrLighthouse2026"},"Ssd":"20260501","Name":"TwrMawrLighthouse2026","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5457397043","FullDateString":"May 1, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Imagine a flower sparking a financial frenzy. Sounds unlikely, right? Yet in the 1630s, tulips did exactly that in the Netherlands. During tulip mania, rare bulbs became luxury items traded for astonishing sums—some valued at prices comparable to a house. Why so valuable? Unusual colours and striped patterns were scarce and unpredictable, and collectors wanted the rarest varieties they could find.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_EN-CA7547956552_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_EN-CA7547956552_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Tulips run the show","Title":"Grape hyacinths and tulips, Keukenhof Gardens, Lisse, Netherlands","Copyright":"© Martin Ruegner/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.26889,4.547222/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.26889,4.547222;S9;Keukenhof Gardens, Lisse, Netherlands&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Keukenhof+Gardens&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260430_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips"},"Ssd":"20260430","Name":"DutchTulips","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7547956552","FullDateString":"Apr. 30, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ships leaving Lisbon once passed a small stone tower before meeting the wide Atlantic. That tower, standing on the bank of the Tagus River, served as both a guardian and a farewell. Say hello to Belém Tower—a fortress that watched Portugal sail into the Age of Exploration.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-CA6523750356_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-CA6523750356_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"History anchored in stone","Title":"Belém Tower on the bank of the Tagus River, Lisbon, Portugal","Copyright":"© f9photos/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.69165,-9.215943/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.69165,-9.215943;S9;Belém Tower, Lisbon, Portugal&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Belem+Tower&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260429_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank"},"Ssd":"20260429","Name":"BelemTowerBank","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6523750356","FullDateString":"Apr. 29, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The spectacled bear, also known as the Andean bear, is the only South American bear of the Ursidae family. Inhabiting the northern and central Andes Mountains, it dwells primarily in forested areas and feeds mainly on shoots and fruit. Pale markings around the eyes often resemble eyeglasses, or 'spectacles,' giving the species its distinctive name.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-CA5387573161_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-CA5387573161_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spectacles in the wild","Title":"Spectacled bear resting in tree, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Each spectacled bear has unique facial markings, which scientists use to identify and track individuals in the wild.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spectacled+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260428_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear"},"Ssd":"20260428","Name":"AndeanBear","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5387573161","FullDateString":"Apr. 28, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Designed by architect Giuseppe Mengoni and completed in 1877, the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II in Milan, Italy, is one of the world's oldest and most famous shopping arcades. Located between Piazza del Duomo and Piazza della Scala, it features a stunning glass-and-iron roof and an elegant, octagonal layout. Affectionately known as 'Milan's living room,' the Galleria is home to high-end boutiques, historic cafés such as Caffè Biffi and Camparino in Galleria, and renowned restaurants.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-CA9394952547_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-CA9394952547_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Glass with class","Title":"The glass dome of Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy","Copyright":"© PhillipMinnis/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/45.466179,9.18992/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=45.466179,9.18992;S9;Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galleria+Vittorio+Emanuele+II+Milan+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260427_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria"},"Ssd":"20260427","Name":"MilanGalleria","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9394952547","FullDateString":"Apr. 27, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring brings apple trees to life with clouds of soft pink blossoms. Their delicate petals brighten orchards and hillsides, standing out against clear blue skies as the season shifts from winter toward warmer days. These blooms attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, helping fruit trees produce the apples that will grow later in the year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-CA6292160620_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-CA6292160620_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bloom boom","Title":"Pink apple blossoms, Avila Beach, California, United States","Copyright":"© Mimi Ditchie Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.177404,-120.733528/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.177404,-120.733528;S9;Avila Beach, California, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Apple+tree&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260426_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260426","Name":"AppleBlossoms","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6292160620","FullDateString":"Apr. 26, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Penguins usually bring Antarctica to mind, but these endearing flightless seabirds don't always follow the ice. On World Penguin Day, the Galápagos penguins pictured here offer a vivid counterpoint. Found only in the Galápagos Islands—a volcanic archipelago about 966 kilometres off Ecuador's coast—this species lives farther north than any other penguin. Cool, nutrient‑rich ocean currents make this equatorial habitat possible by supplying food and keeping surrounding waters within survivable temperatures. Compact and agile, these birds spend much of the day in the water to stay cool.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-CA5860211884_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-CA5860211884_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Breaking the penguin rules","Title":"Galápagos penguins swimming, Galápagos Islands, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Henley Spiers/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-0.859397,-91.215904/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-0.859397,-91.215904;S9;Galápagos Islands, Ecuador&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Penguin+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260425_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins"},"Ssd":"20260425","Name":"GalapagosPenguins","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5860211884","FullDateString":"Apr. 25, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"It starts quietly—rows of tulips opening along the Rideau Canal as spring settles in. Then the story catches up. The Canadian Tulip Festival begins today, marking its 74th year, but its roots go back to wartime Europe. In 1945, after Canada helped liberate the Netherlands and hosted Princess Juliana during her exile, a gift of tulip bulbs arrived in Ottawa. That tradition didn't end; it returned each year, growing into today's festival.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TulipFestOT_EN-CA8431484438_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TulipFestOT_EN-CA8431484438_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"When Ottawa turns tulip","Title":"Tulips and cherry blossoms at the Rideau Canal, Ottawa, Ontario","Copyright":"© J Duquette/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"There are over 3,000 registered tulip varieties.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260508_TulipFestOT\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Canadian+Tulip+Festival&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260508_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260508_TulipFestOT"},"Ssd":"20260508","Name":"TulipFestOT","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"8431484438","FullDateString":"May 8, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Stretching across the Sonoran Desert in southwestern Arizona, Kofa National Wildlife Refuge is a land of sharp peaks, wide skies and surprising life. The refuge was established in 1939 to protect desert bighorn sheep, whose sure-footed silhouettes still define the rugged landscape.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Kofa_EN-CA1760783023_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Kofa_EN-CA1760783023_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Desert, drawn wide","Title":"Kofa National Wildlife Refuge, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Denis Tangney Jr/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/33.237633,-114.011215/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=33.237633,-114.011215;S9;Kofa National Wildlife Refuge, Arizona, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260507_Kofa\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Kofa+National+Wildlife+Refuge&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260507_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260507_Kofa"},"Ssd":"20260507","Name":"Kofa","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"1760783023","FullDateString":"May 7, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Located on the eastern Balkan Peninsula, Bulgaria sits at the crossroads of Europe and Asia, where ancient cultures, fertile landscapes and shifting climates converge.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_EN-CA6379116198_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_EN-CA6379116198_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Plains under pressure","Title":"Thunderstorm above the plains, Bulgaria","Copyright":"© Revolu7ion93/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.75,25.5/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.75,25.5;S9;Bulgaria&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bulgaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260506_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains"},"Ssd":"20260506","Name":"BulgariaPlains","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6379116198","FullDateString":"May 6, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Not one to hurry, a bull moose moves with steady purpose—and for good reason. As part of the North American moose population native to Canada, these animals are well adapted to long winters and short growing seasons. Their diet shifts with availability: in summer, they browse fresh leaves, shrubs and aquatic plants; in winter, they rely more on woody material like twigs and bark.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BullQuebec_EN-CA5955231847_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BullQuebec_EN-CA5955231847_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"In step with the forest","Title":"A majestic bull moose foraging through the green undergrowth, Quebec","Copyright":"© pchoui/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Moose are excellent swimmers and are known to wade into water to eat aquatic plants.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260505_BullQuebec\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Moose+animal&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260505_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260505_BullQuebec"},"Ssd":"20260505","Name":"BullQuebec","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5955231847","FullDateString":"May 5, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"May the 4th be with you! On Star Wars Day, reality cosplays as science fiction and dares you to tell the difference. Our image takes us to Ksar Ouled Soltane in Tunisia's Tataouine district, where stacked clay granaries rise like sand‑coloured fortresses. Dating back to the 15th century, this storehouse complex was built by Berber communities to protect harvests from heat, theft and time. Function first. Beauty as a side effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_EN-CA5863757495_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_EN-CA5863757495_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Sci‑fi, Earth‑made","Title":"Ksar Ouled Soltane, Tataouine district in southern Tunisia","Copyright":"© Dark_Eni/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/32.793106,10.518624/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=32.793106,10.518624;S9;Ksar Ouled Soltane, Tataouine, Tunisia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Star+Wars+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260504_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane"},"Ssd":"20260504","Name":"KsarOuledSoltane","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5863757495","FullDateString":"May 4, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"High above the savannah in Kenya's Masai Mara, a leopard curls up on a tree branch, napping as the grasslands glow at sunset. On International Leopard Day, observed on May 3, we celebrate one of the world's most adaptable big cats. Leopards roam across Africa and parts of Asia, thriving in habitats that range from forests and mountains to open savannahs. Their spotted coats are unique to each individual, like fingerprints, and their powerful climbing skills allow them to stash prey high in trees, out of reach of scavengers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_EN-CA1789008589_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_EN-CA1789008589_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Savannah afterglow","Title":"Leopard sleeping in a tree in the savannah, Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Leopards have lost about 75% of their historical distribution and are classified as 'vulnerable' by the IUCN.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Leopard+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260503_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard"},"Ssd":"20260503","Name":"MasaiLeopard","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"1789008589","FullDateString":"May 3, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Can you picture 11,000 square kilometres of protected wilderness? That's Jasper National Park in Alberta. Established in 1907 as part of a growing network of protected landscapes in the Canadian Rockies, it was designated a national park in 1930. The park reflects both conservation efforts and much older Indigenous connections, including those of the Nakoda and Secwépemc peoples. Its terrain ranges from glacier-fed rivers and alpine meadows to dense conifer forests dominated by spruce and pine.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GreenJasper_EN-CA5522153954_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GreenJasper_EN-CA5522153954_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The magic of Jasper","Title":"Small lake and marsh in Jasper National Park in Alberta","Copyright":"© Don White/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.873398,-117.954308/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.873398,-117.954308;S9;Jasper National Park, Alberta&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260502_GreenJasper\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Jasper+National+Park+Alberta&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260502_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260502_GreenJasper"},"Ssd":"20260502","Name":"GreenJasper","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5522153954","FullDateString":"May 2, 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Image of the day","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Learn more","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donate now","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Quick fact:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Recent Homepage images","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Homepage image for {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"On this day in history","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"On this day in {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPA